\c 40
\s1 Mazmur yang ditulis Daud untuk pemimpin pujian
\q1
\v 1 Pada TUHAN aku bergantung,
\q2 dan didengar-Nya teriakanku meminta tolong.
\q1
\v 2 Diangkat-Nya aku dari lembah kematian.
\q2 Dari lumpur yang dalam, diangkat-Nya aku;
\q1 Dikokohkan-Nya tempat aku berdiri,
\q2 diamankan-Nya jalanku.
\q1
\v 3 Diletakkan-Nya lagu baru dalam mulutku,
\q2 suatu pujian bagi Allah kita.
\q1 Banyak orang akan terkejut,
\q2 dan menjadi takut lalu percaya kepada Dia.
\b
\q1
\v 4 TUHAN senang pada mereka yang percaya pada-Nya,
\q2 mereka yang tidak percaya kepada ilah-ilah
\q2 atau yang menyembah dewa-dewa.
\q1
\v 5 Ya TUHAN, Allahku, betapa ajaib perbuatan-Mu!
\q2 Tidak seorangpun yang sebanding dengan Engkau.
\q1 Jika aku hendak menceritakan semua perbuatan ajaib-Mu,
\q1 Aku tidak bisa melakukannya,
\q2 terlalu banyak perbuatan-Mu yang ajaib.
\b
\q1
\v 6 Engkau tidak berkenan kepada korban bakaran dan persembahan.
\q2 Engkau membuat diriku mengerti.
\q1 \add Korban persembahan dan bakaran tidaklah bisa menghapuskan dosa.\add*
\q1
\v 7 Inilah tutur kataku, “TUHAN, inilah aku,
\q2 \add aku hendak melakukan perintah-perintah-Mu,\add*
\q2 hal-hal yang menjadi kehendak-Mu.”
\q1
\v 8 Ya Allahku, aku bersuka melakukan kehendak-Mu;
\q2 Dalam hatiku kusimpan hukum-hukum-Mu.
\b
\q1
\v 9 Kapanpun umat-Mu berkumpul,
\q2 I have told them about how you save us.
\q2 Yahweh, you know that I have not refused to tell that to them.
\q1
\v 10 And I have not kept within me the news that you always act justly/fairly;
\q2 when many of your people have gathered together \add to worship you in thetemple\add*,
\q1 I have told them that you are faithful to us and save us.
\q2 I have not concealed that you faithfully love us and act loyally toward us.
\b
\q1
\v 11 Yahweh, do not stop acting mercifully toward me.
\q2 Because you faithfully love me [PRS] and are loyal to me, always protect me.
\q1
\v 12 I have many troubles; I cannot count them.
\q2 My sins are like a flood that has covered me [PRS, MET];
\q2 \add they are so many that\add* I cannot see \add all of them\add*.
\q1 The sins that I have committed are more than the hairs on my head.
\q2 I am very discouraged.
\b
\q1
\v 13 O Yahweh, please save me!
\q2 Come quickly to help me!
\q1
\v 14 Humble those who are happy about my troubles, and cause them to be disgraced and ashamed.
\q2 Chase away those who are trying to get rid of me.
\q1
\v 15 I hope/desire that those who make fun of me
\q2 will be dismayed when you defeat them.
\q1
\v 16 But I hope that all those who go to \add worship\add* you will be very joyful [DOU].
\q2 I hope/desire that those who love you because you saved them will shout repeatedly,
\q1 “Yahweh is great!”
\b
\q1
\v 17 As for me, I am poor and needy [DOU];
\q2 but \add I know that\add* Yahweh has not forgotten me.
\q1 O my God, you are the one who saves and helps me,
\q2 so please come quickly \add and help me\add*!